The cabinet shall prioritize the applications based on the following factors:
The project's consistency with the purposes of the waste tire program;
The project's costs and forecasted benefits;
The applicant's credit history; and
The applicant's and key personnel's environmental compliance record.

A person awarded a grant shall:
Construct and operate the project in compliance with this chapter and the grant conditions;
Remain responsible for complying with this chapter and the grant conditions, even if the project is managed by someone else;
Retain ownership of all real and personal property purchased with grant funds unless the cabinet approves their transfer;
Submit to the cabinet monthly an itemized list of expenditures, with copies of invoices or similar documentation;
Submit to the cabinet periodic progress reports; and
Not change the project without the cabinet's approval.
